						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1439, Īśvara, Māgha, śu. 5,</hi> corresponding <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1518 January 16, Saturday</hi> (not verifiable). It records that <hi rend="bold">Rāmaṇa-Nāyaka,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Kaṭhāri Tippaṇa-Nāyaka,</hi> who was an officer of <hi rend="bold">Prauḍha-Dēvarāya-Mahārāya,</hi> constructed the temple of the god Prasanna-Rāmayadēva and consecrated the image of the god in it.</p>						

